WEBVTT

00:01.930 --> 00:05.696
Previously on Elementary...
I heard the refrigerator door
open, and then all of a sudden,

00:05.730 --> 00:07.698
three gunshots,
and I saw

00:07.740 --> 00:11.301
Jameel on the kitchen floor,
blood everthere.

00:11.340 --> 00:14.070
I know you killed Jameel Clark.
WATSON: He's worked for months

00:14.110 --> 00:16.078
to embed himself in SBK.
An endeavor I cared more about

00:16.110 --> 00:17.600
before I knew he was
a cold-blooded killer.

00:17.650 --> 00:19.174
SBK is a ruthless drug gang.

00:21.420 --> 00:24.082
You want to know who killed
Jameel? SBK killed Jameel.

00:24.120 --> 00:26.088
You're looking for someone
who killed one person.

00:26.120 --> 00:28.418
SBK kills dozens
of people a year.

00:28.460 --> 00:29.620
I'm-a take SBK down,

00:29.660 --> 00:31.787
and anybody who get in my way...
(grunts)

00:31.830 --> 00:33.354
...gonna get hurt.

00:39.140 --> 00:41.096
WOMAN: Sherlock,
I thought you were

00:41.140 --> 00:42.835
coming right back to...

00:42.870 --> 00:44.508
Oh, my God.

00:44.540 --> 00:47.100
Look at you.

00:47.140 --> 00:50.143
I didn't do any of that, did I?

00:50.180 --> 00:51.772
No, no, no.

00:51.810 --> 00:54.415
You didn't leave a scratch.

00:54.450 --> 00:57.442
Well, the night
is still young.

00:57.490 --> 00:59.481
I'll be right there.

01:14.800 --> 01:16.563
WATSON :
Hey.

01:16.610 --> 01:18.498
If I went downstairs
to get a coffee, would I be...

01:18.540 --> 01:20.132
No, my guest
left hours ago.

01:20.180 --> 01:21.670
Oh. Good.

01:21.710 --> 01:23.678
Do I detect just
a hint of judgment?

01:23.710 --> 01:24.802
No, no judgment.

01:24.850 --> 01:27.114
A little concern, maybe.

01:27.150 --> 01:29.243
Well, despite what you may
have heard, no one was injured.

01:29.290 --> 01:31.383
I am fighting off something
of a head cold, though.

01:31.420 --> 01:34.116
That's not what I meant.

01:34.160 --> 01:35.855
There have been a lot

01:35.890 --> 01:38.779
of guests this week,
and I can't help but think

01:38.830 --> 01:41.253
that there might be
more effective ways

01:41.300 --> 01:44.121
to work through everything
that went down with Shinwell.

01:44.170 --> 01:45.762
Since everything
went down with Shinwell,

01:45.800 --> 01:47.267
you've cleaned
your office twice,

01:47.300 --> 01:48.597
you've taken
three remedial cases,

01:48.640 --> 01:50.301
and then you cleaned
your office again.

01:50.340 --> 01:53.730
So is that the picture of mental
health I should aspire to?

01:53.780 --> 01:55.407
Well, the captain
hasn't had anything

01:55.440 --> 01:56.907
you've deemed interesting
this week,

01:56.950 --> 01:58.577
so I know myself.

01:58.610 --> 01:59.645
I like to keep busy.

01:59.680 --> 02:01.409
So working is working for me.

02:01.450 --> 02:02.883
We misjudged a murderer;

02:02.920 --> 02:04.615
we let him into
our closest confidence.

02:04.650 --> 02:06.811
And then I betrayed our
colleagues by destroying

02:06.860 --> 02:08.816
evidence that would_ have
returned hIm to prison.

02:08.860 --> 02:10.885
And he repaid our many
kindnesses by ambushing

02:10.930 --> 02:12.329
and severely beating me.

02:12.360 --> 02:14.225
You've made peace
with all of that?

02:14.260 --> 02:16.797
No, I've just come to accept
that we don't have any options.

02:16.830 --> 02:18.821
There's no way to prove
that Shinwell is a killer,

02:18.870 --> 02:21.862
so unless you want to go to SBK
and out him as an informant...

02:21.900 --> 02:24.209
No, I'd still rather
he wipe out a street gang

02:24.240 --> 02:25.867
than the other way around.

02:25.910 --> 02:27.832
Okay, so we move on.

02:27.880 --> 02:29.871
I'm gonna go down
to the precinct,

02:29.910 --> 02:31.400
see ifI can lend a hand with
whatever they're working on.

02:31.450 --> 02:32.815
You want to come?
No.

02:32.850 --> 02:35.341
Perfunctory investigation
will do me no good, Watson.

02:35.380 --> 02:36.938
To clean out the cobwebs,

02:36.990 --> 02:39.208
I need something
truly stimulating.

02:42.260 --> 02:43.557
(grunting)

02:52.900 --> 02:56.768
First up,
Mr. Gary Kalajian.

02:59.380 --> 03:02.599
Marco, did you pull
a shift this weekend?

03:02.650 --> 03:06.313
We were closed. Why?

03:07.880 --> 03:11.247
When I closed on Friday,
this cremator was clean.

03:14.990 --> 03:16.287
Oh, my God.

03:23.800 --> 03:25.529
Call the police.

03:27.540 --> 03:30.805
Now.

03:30.840 --> 03:32.637
What should I tell them?

03:32.680 --> 03:35.979
Tell them somebody
got burned alive here.

03:39.850 --> 03:42.387
*

04:04.740 --> 04:06.605
It's a good thing femurs
are as thick as they are.

04:06.640 --> 04:08.437
The biggest bones didn't
burn down completely.

04:08.480 --> 04:09.947
It's the only way
I could tell that there were

04:09.980 --> 04:13.746
_ two victims stuffed
Into the crematory furnace.

04:13.780 --> 04:15.919
Looks like both were male.
Good eye.

04:15.950 --> 04:17.542
You can tell by the width
of the intertrochanteric crest.

04:17.590 --> 04:20.889
Whoever they were,
one of them left a handprint

04:20.920 --> 04:22.626
just inside
the incinerator door.

04:22.660 --> 04:23.957
HAWES:
It's over eight inches long.

04:23.990 --> 04:25.457
He was probably tall.

04:25.490 --> 04:27.958
And alive when he went
into the incinerator.

04:28.000 --> 04:29.592
Here. Have a nightmare.

04:29.630 --> 04:31.427
BELL: The blood was smeared
and then cooked, so...

04:31.470 --> 04:33.392
No fingerprints.

04:33.440 --> 04:35.431
I'm guessing you would have
invited us to the scene

04:35.470 --> 04:36.368
if there was
something to see.

04:36.410 --> 04:39.504
_ Rear exit_door was
pried open With a crowbar.

04:39.540 --> 04:41.508
The break-in happened
sometime over the weekend.

04:41.540 --> 04:43.440
The crematorium workers
all have aIIbIS,

04:43.480 --> 04:45.368
and we couldn't find anybody
who works in the area

04:45.410 --> 04:46.570
who saw anything suspicious.

04:46.620 --> 04:48.349
WATSON:
No security cameras?

04:48.380 --> 04:50.416
BELL: The owner says
they create privacy issues.

04:50.450 --> 04:52.486
We got nothing.

04:52.520 --> 04:53.817
HAWES:
Only if you don't count

04:53.860 --> 04:56.749
two piles of dust,
teeth and bone fragments.

04:56.790 --> 04:57.882
And whatever these are.

04:57.930 --> 04:59.818
HAWES: Those were found
at the back of the incinerator,

04:59.860 --> 05:01.828
near where the taller
John Doe's feet were.

05:01.860 --> 05:03.919
I'm pretty sure they were
an orthopedic brace

05:03.970 --> 05:05.062
that melted down.

05:05.100 --> 05:07.568
Uh, something
like this.

05:08.870 --> 05:10.531
We should check with
Missmg Persons,

05:10.570 --> 05:13.368
see if anyone's been
reported who wears one.

05:13.410 --> 05:16.402
We should also start calling
dentists in Dongan Hills.

05:16.450 --> 05:17.576
If I'm right about this,

05:17.610 --> 05:19.942
we need to locate
the dental records

05:19.980 --> 05:21.743
of one Frederick Kirby,

05:21.780 --> 05:25.079
and see if we get a match
for that gold tooth.

05:25.120 --> 05:26.849
Are you saying
you know one of these guys?

05:26.890 --> 05:28.482
After a fashion.

05:28.520 --> 05:30.078
Mr. Kirby was likely

05:30.130 --> 05:32.928
the worst private investigator
in New York City.

05:36.670 --> 05:39.434
(door bells jingle)

05:39.470 --> 05:40.892
BELL:
Well, it's official.

05:40.940 --> 05:43.465
Captain just got the call.

05:43.510 --> 05:45.705
The gold incisor
and a couple of the molars

05:45.740 --> 05:47.105
and the smaller pile of ash

05:47.140 --> 05:48.539
match Fred Kirby's
dental records.

05:48.580 --> 05:50.741
Which means it took you
all of ten minutes

05:50.780 --> 05:53.112
to identify a John Doe
who'd been burnt to powder.

05:53.150 --> 05:55.710
That's got to be a record.
No, it was nothing.

05:55.750 --> 05:56.944
How many men do you know
proudly wear

05:56.990 --> 05:58.719
a high school class ring?

05:58.750 --> 06:00.615
Uh, you never told us
how you knew him.

06:00.660 --> 06:03.823
He came by the brownstone once,
accused me of poaching.

06:03.860 --> 06:06.590
You stole one of his clients?

06:06.630 --> 06:08.791
No, I was cornered by
a dissatisfied customer of his.

06:08.830 --> 06:10.718
I took one look
at Mr. Kirby's files,

06:10.770 --> 06:12.169
solved the case
on the spot.

06:12.200 --> 06:14.589
I've never seen such
shoddy detective work.

06:14.640 --> 06:15.834
(phone chimes)

06:15.870 --> 06:17.531
This place is
a temple of incompetence.

06:17.570 --> 06:19.037
According to
the captain,

06:19.070 --> 06:21.800
this guy's one employee
is missing, too.

06:21.840 --> 06:24.172
The name's Lamont Wallace,
but he goes by "Pinlq."

06:24.210 --> 06:26.542
Started driving for Fred
a couple years ago

06:26.580 --> 06:28.673
when Fred's eyes
started to go.

06:28.720 --> 06:31.985
A legally blind private eye.
No comment.

06:32.020 --> 06:33.556
No one's been
able to get

06:33.590 --> 06:35.808
either of them on the phone
for two days.

06:35.860 --> 06:37.521
Well, Lamont's a big guy.

06:37.560 --> 06:40.028
Could have been his handprint
in the incinerator.

06:40.060 --> 06:41.857
Yeah, maybe he and Fred
took on a dangerous case

06:41.900 --> 06:42.889
that got them both killed.

06:44.730 --> 06:46.732
You got something?

06:46.770 --> 06:50.558
There_'s_almost a dozen
restraining orders here.

06:54.680 --> 06:58.002
These are all filed
within days of each other.

06:58.050 --> 07:00.518
Yeah, none of the complainants
have the same last name,

07:00.550 --> 07:02.586
but it's got to be a
coordinated effort, right?

07:02.620 --> 07:04.542
BELL:
You'd think.

07:04.590 --> 07:07.514
Question is: what's the
link between these people?

07:07.560 --> 07:09.152
Tragedy.

07:10.990 --> 07:13.550
HOLMES: I assume you're familiar
with the shooting spree

07:13.600 --> 07:16.125
that occurred at
the Bennett Courthouse in 1987?

07:16.160 --> 07:18.094
Guy shoots a bunch
of brand-new citizens

07:18.130 --> 07:19.961
after a swearing-in ceremony.

07:20.000 --> 07:21.968
His wife was their
CIVICS teacher, rIght?

07:22.000 --> 07:24.639
Four people dead,
six more wounded,

07:24.670 --> 07:26.831
and the shooter ended up
taking his own life.

07:26.880 --> 07:29.542
It was a tragedy, not a mystery.

07:29.580 --> 07:31.946
So what's it got to do
with a detective and his buddy

07:31.980 --> 07:33.971
getting burnt alive
30 years later?

07:34.020 --> 07:35.510
In Fred Kirby's office,

07:35.550 --> 07:37.518
we found multiple
restraining orders against him.

07:37.550 --> 07:40.212
All of them were filed by
family members of the victims

07:40.260 --> 07:41.613
of the courthouse shooting.

07:41.660 --> 07:43.525
It appears that Mr. Kirby
reached out

07:43.560 --> 07:46.529
to anyone tangentially
associated with the shooting.

07:46.560 --> 07:48.699
To what end, we don't know.

07:48.730 --> 07:50.527
You talk to any
of these people yet?

07:50.570 --> 07:53.664
No. Watson's on her way
to speak to Virginia Spivey.

07:53.700 --> 07:56.533
She was married to the hero
bailiff who charged the gunman.

07:56.570 --> 07:59.038
Took a bullet that
day, but survived.

07:59.070 --> 08:01.573
Unfortunately, he died
of lymphoma last year.

08:01.610 --> 08:04.738
Virginia Spivey was
the first one to file.

08:04.780 --> 08:07.146
You think papering him
with Orders of Protection

08:07.180 --> 08:08.738
was her idea?
That's the hope.

08:08.780 --> 08:10.816
If she was in touch
with all of these people,

08:10.850 --> 08:13.614
perhaps she'll be able to tell
us if any of them would have

08:13.660 --> 08:16.754
been likely to have cremated
Fred Kirby and his helper.

08:16.790 --> 08:18.155
In the meantime, Marcus and I

08:18.190 --> 08:19.794
are going to visit
the Bennett Courthouse.

08:19.830 --> 08:22.094
Why? The shooting happened
decades ago.

08:22.130 --> 08:23.722
What do you think
you're gonna find?

08:23.770 --> 08:26.591
This was in
Fred's office.

08:29.040 --> 08:31.099
Court employee badge.

08:31.140 --> 08:32.539
It's a sloppy forgery.

08:32.580 --> 08:34.104
I'm going to
chalk up the alias

08:34.140 --> 08:36.108
to his overheated sense
of whimsy.

08:36.140 --> 08:37.607
But I would
like to know

08:37.650 --> 08:38.844
why he deemed it necessary

08:38.880 --> 08:41.144
to go undercover
at the courthouse.

08:43.150 --> 08:44.947
Mr. Holmes.

08:44.990 --> 08:47.185
Louis Garmendia.

08:47.220 --> 08:51.725
I wish it wasn't such a sad
occasron that we got together.

08:51.760 --> 08:54.251
But it is an honor
to finally meet you.

08:54.300 --> 08:56.962
You know me?
Of_ course. I'm
Lours Garmendia.

08:57.000 --> 09:00.128
President of the New York
Order of Private Investigators.

09:00.170 --> 09:03.298
Oh, the silver star
people-- NYOOPI.

09:03.340 --> 09:04.864
Yeah, that's us.

09:04.910 --> 09:07.777
So, are you responsible
for their, uh,

09:07.810 --> 09:09.744
rise in prominence?

09:09.780 --> 09:11.668
Well, I don't know if I can
really take credit for that.

09:11.710 --> 09:13.018
I just took over.

09:13.050 --> 09:15.109
But that is how I knew Fred.

09:15.150 --> 09:16.788
And, obviously,
we're all broken up

09:16.820 --> 09:18.344
over what happened to him.

09:18.390 --> 09:19.857
Mm.
Amway,

09:19.890 --> 09:21.949
as president,
I just wanted to come down

09:21.990 --> 09:24.754
and let you know you've got
the association's full support.

09:24.790 --> 09:27.224
Anything you
or the department needs,

09:27.260 --> 09:28.750
you say the word.

09:28.800 --> 09:30.199
All right, well, I'll be sure
to pass that along.

09:30.230 --> 09:33.893
Mai_n reason I came down
IS to say thank you.

09:33.940 --> 09:37.205
Means a lot to have one of our
own working this thing for Fred.

09:37.240 --> 09:39.128
Sorry, one of your own?

09:39.170 --> 09:40.603
NYOOPI members.

09:40.640 --> 09:41.902
You and your partner.

09:41.940 --> 09:44.738
Feels right
keeping it in the family.

09:44.780 --> 09:48.876
Remind me, how long have
we been in the family?

09:48.920 --> 09:51.218
WATSON:
So, Houston, you were a pitcher?

09:51.250 --> 09:52.649
JOSH:
He still is.

09:52.690 --> 09:55.113
Lowest ERA in
Division II.

09:55.160 --> 09:56.684
You know
St. Cassius College?

09:56.730 --> 09:58.288
You should come see
us play sometime.

09:58.330 --> 10:01.094
Did you not hear her tell my mom
she's with the police?

10:01.130 --> 10:03.394
JOSH: What, police
don't like baseball?

10:03.430 --> 10:06.092
All right, guys,
that's the rest. (chuckles)

10:06.130 --> 10:07.688
Everything's okay, right?

10:07.740 --> 10:10.800
Everything's fine.
I'm just here to talk.

10:10.840 --> 10:12.000
You two drive safe.

10:12.040 --> 10:13.803
Thanks, Mrs. Spivey.

10:13.840 --> 10:16.274
Very nice meeting you.

10:18.280 --> 10:20.111
Sorry about that.
(chuckles)

10:20.150 --> 10:22.641
But you said you wanted to talk
about the courthouse shooting,

10:22.690 --> 10:24.419
and it seemed like
I should get the boys

10:24.450 --> 10:26.850
on their way first.
Of course.

10:26.890 --> 10:28.687
I was just wondering about
some of the contact

10:28.720 --> 10:31.120
you might have had recently with
the other victims' families.

10:31.160 --> 10:32.991
I've had a lot, actually.

10:33.030 --> 10:34.292
More than usual.

10:34.330 --> 10:36.821
The 30th anniversary
was last month,

10:36.870 --> 10:39.327
and, uh, well, you can probably
tell I like remembrances.

10:39.370 --> 10:40.837
We raised a
little money

10:40.870 --> 10:43.703
and did a memorial exhibit
at the courthouse.

10:43.740 --> 10:44.968
Something to make sure

10:45.010 --> 10:46.739
the people who died
aren't forgotten.

10:47.740 --> 10:48.809
Well, here.

10:54.480 --> 10:57.381
Looks like you did
some great work.

10:57.420 --> 10:59.786
I wanted to do it years ago,
but Gordon, my husband,

10:59.820 --> 11:01.048
he wouldn't have it.

11:01.090 --> 11:03.354
He passed away
last year,

11:03.390 --> 11:06.382
so now he can't object
to being remembered as a hero.

11:06.430 --> 11:07.795
Which he was.

11:07.830 --> 11:09.422
If he hadn't charged
the shooter,

11:09.460 --> 11:11.121
well, let's just say

11:11.170 --> 11:13.468
that would've been_
a much bigger memorial.

11:13.500 --> 11:17.106
Am I correct that you
and some of the other families

11:17.140 --> 11:20.303
filed restraining orders
against a man named Fred Kirby?

11:20.340 --> 11:22.877
Yeah.
He was bothering all of us.

11:22.910 --> 11:24.741
Said he was trying
to put together

11:26.880 --> 11:28.313
His story kept changing.

11:28.350 --> 11:31.478
It was weird, so I got a lawyer
to shut him down.

11:31.520 --> 11:33.852
And I told the others
to do the same.

11:33.890 --> 11:35.084
Is that why you're here?

11:35.120 --> 11:37.088
Has he done
something illegal?

11:37.130 --> 11:39.223
He died this past weekend.

11:39.260 --> 11:41.820
Uh, more specifically,
he was murdered.

11:41.860 --> 11:42.895
Oh, my God.

11:42.930 --> 11:44.795
You think one of us...?

11:44.830 --> 11:46.889
I'm just curious. Is it possible
that any of the people

11:46.940 --> 11:48.498
he was harassing might've been
angry enough to...

11:48.540 --> 11:50.428
Uh, no. No, not a chance.

11:50.470 --> 11:52.267
He wasn't harassing anyone,

11:52.310 --> 11:55.871
he just wanted stuff
that belonged to the victims.

11:55.910 --> 11:57.400
We think he was a collector,

11:57.450 --> 11:58.405
or maybe a dealer.

11:58.450 --> 11:59.940
A dealer?

11:59.980 --> 12:01.868
You ever heard the term
"murderabilia"?

12:01.920 --> 12:03.888
People buy and sell

12:03.920 --> 12:05.911
I guess you'd
call them artifacts

12:05.950 --> 12:09.488
that connect back _
to famous murders or tragedies.

12:09.520 --> 12:11.420
It's pretty sick.

12:11.460 --> 12:14.258
We just thought Fred
was trying to make a buck.

12:14.300 --> 12:16.222
He should've been ashamed
of himself.

12:16.260 --> 12:17.864
But trust me.

12:17.900 --> 12:20.892
None of us
would've killed the guy.

12:20.940 --> 12:22.908
(door closes, lock clicks)

12:22.940 --> 12:24.362
Hey. I'm home.

12:30.250 --> 12:32.002
What do you think?

12:32.050 --> 12:34.348
I think there's a bus bench

12:34.380 --> 12:37.019
with my picture on it
in the library.

12:37.050 --> 12:38.984
I used
Fred Kirby's guy.

12:39.020 --> 12:40.954
It was a rush job,
so it wasn't cheap,

12:40.990 --> 12:42.457
but he threw in
the bench for free.

12:42.490 --> 12:45.425
So are you gonna tell me
what this is about, or...?

12:45.460 --> 12:46.950
NYOOPI.

12:48.130 --> 12:50.894
N-Y-O-O-P-I,

12:50.930 --> 12:54.388
the absurd acronym for an even
more absurd organization--

12:54.440 --> 12:56.829
one which _counts us both
as members in good standing.

12:56.870 --> 12:58.235
Oh, yeah.

12:58.270 --> 12:59.806
The detective thing.

12:59.840 --> 13:01.899
Yeah, "the detective thing."

13:01.940 --> 13:04.079
I don't get it.

13:04.110 --> 13:06.146
Are you angry
because I signed us up?

13:06.180 --> 13:07.977
So you don't deny it.

13:08.020 --> 13:10.011
Yeah, it was years ago.
You'd gone back to London.

13:10.050 --> 13:11.847
When you came back, I added you.

13:11.890 --> 13:13.312
It's free advertising.

13:13.360 --> 13:15.055
They put us on
the "Find a Detective" page

13:15.090 --> 13:16.216
on their Web site.

13:16.260 --> 13:17.352
That is precisely the problem:

13:17.390 --> 13:19.028
I do not care
for the association.

13:19.060 --> 13:19.685
Why?

13:19.730 --> 13:21.857
Because the group is a sham.

13:21.900 --> 13:23.891
They've completely usurped
the New York State

13:23.930 --> 13:25.488
Division of Licensing Services

13:25.530 --> 13:28.533
and destroyed all semblance
of standards in our profession.

13:28.570 --> 13:30.208
What are you talking about?

13:30.240 --> 13:32.458
Once upon a time,
every aspiring P.I.

13:32.510 --> 13:35.070
had to take an exam
administered by the state.

13:35.110 --> 13:37.249
It wasn't terribly difficult,
but it was something.

13:37.280 --> 13:41.046
It was a barrier to entry
to keep the riffraff out.

13:41.080 --> 13:42.149
Now Internet searches
have become

13:42.180 --> 13:44.512
the primary arbiter of
legitimacy in every profession.

13:44.550 --> 13:46.859
So this... this star

13:46.890 --> 13:49.358
is all you need
to be a detective in New York.

13:49.390 --> 13:54.020
For $278 in annual fees,
anyone can advertise using this,

13:54.060 --> 13:56.358
and gain access to NYOOPI's
all-important Web site.

13:56.400 --> 13:59.028
So here, have your pick.

13:59.070 --> 14:02.392
Disgraced FBI agents,
idiots off the street, me.

14:02.440 --> 14:05.466
We are all equal
in the eyes of this group.

14:07.510 --> 14:08.977
You're being a snob.

14:09.010 --> 14:10.978
Someone has to be.

14:11.010 --> 14:12.307
Did you get my
text earlier,

14:12.350 --> 14:13.977
about why Fred Kirby
might have been harassing

14:14.020 --> 14:15.942
Virginia Spivey and the others?

14:15.980 --> 14:18.016
I did.
Well, I spent the
afternoon online,

14:18.050 --> 14:20.314
looking at
murderabilia auctions.

14:20.360 --> 14:23.625
I didn't see anything there on
the Bennett Courthouse shooting.

14:23.660 --> 14:26.322
So I also looked at
Kirby's financials.

14:26.360 --> 14:28.248
It didn't look like he ever sold
that kind of stuff,

14:28.300 --> 14:30.962
so it makes me wonder why he was
so interested in what happened.

14:31.000 --> 14:32.422
It's a good question.

14:32.470 --> 14:34.529
I might be able
to shed some light.

14:36.370 --> 14:38.201
In 1987,

14:38.240 --> 14:40.504
when new citizens were sworn in
at the Bennett Courthouse,

14:40.540 --> 14:42.371
it was customary to give them
pocket-sized copies

14:42.410 --> 14:45.049
of the Constitution.

14:45.080 --> 14:48.174
These were on display
at Ms. Spivey's memorial.

14:48.220 --> 14:50.188
I borrowed them,
along with

14:50.220 --> 14:53.018
this photograph of the victims
taken shortly before

14:53.060 --> 14:54.118
the shooting started.

14:54.160 --> 14:57.618
Now, this is photograph
was taken when the memorial

14:57.660 --> 14:59.218
first opened last month.

14:59.260 --> 15:01.296
Notice the blood color
and patterns

15:01.330 --> 15:03.093
on these Constitutions.

15:06.000 --> 15:07.592
These are different.

15:07.640 --> 15:10.108
Mm. The blood that you're
looking at is fake.

15:10.140 --> 15:13.439
These are reproductions.

15:13.480 --> 15:16.574
They are also laden with
Fred Kirby's fingerprints.

15:16.610 --> 15:18.271
So he swapped these
Constitutions out

15:18.310 --> 15:20.619
for the real ones; he got
his murderabilia after all.

15:20.650 --> 15:23.084
Yes, but perhaps
not to sell.

15:23.120 --> 15:24.985
What do you mean?

15:25.020 --> 15:27.113
I mean, it's possible
Fred Kirby did what he did

15:27.160 --> 15:28.559
because he believed
the US. government

15:28.590 --> 15:31.081
once caused a nuclear reactor
to melt down.

15:31.130 --> 15:32.586
Just as it's possible

15:32.630 --> 15:35.121
that testing his theory
resulted in his murder.

15:35.160 --> 15:36.457
What are you talking about?

15:36.500 --> 15:40.095
I'm talking, Watson,
about Chernobyl.

15:51.050 --> 15:52.506
HOLMES:
On April 26, 1986,

15:52.550 --> 15:55.576
a test of the Chernobyl power
plant's safety system went awry,

15:55.620 --> 15:58.646
causing one of its
nuclear reactors to explode.

15:58.690 --> 16:01.158
I remember. Everyone remembers.

16:01.190 --> 16:03.158
The blast
and the radiation exposure

16:03.190 --> 16:04.350
killed dozens that day.

16:04.390 --> 16:07.029
Eventually, thousands more
died of cancer.

16:07.060 --> 16:10.063
Human error was cited
as the preCIpitating cause.

16:10.100 --> 16:13.160
The official report
did not name any names.

16:13.200 --> 16:15.088
But according to one theory
on the Internet,

16:15.140 --> 16:18.701
the fault lies with four men:
Igor Krasnaia, Roman Hubenko,

16:18.740 --> 16:21.038
Dmitry Perov
and Sergei Minkovski.

16:21.080 --> 16:22.479
Their bodies
were never recovered,

16:22.510 --> 16:25.047
and photographs of the men
do not exist.

16:25.080 --> 16:26.104
Okay.

16:26.150 --> 16:27.174
Conspiracy theorists

16:27.220 --> 16:29.438
have long believed
that these men were saboteurs,

16:29.480 --> 16:32.119
working at the behest
of the American government.

16:32.150 --> 16:34.710
In return for their crimes,
they were granted new lives

16:34.760 --> 16:37.388
in the United States.

16:37.430 --> 16:39.125
Those were the four men
that were killed

16:39.160 --> 16:40.149
in the Bennett Courthouse
shoobng?

16:40.200 --> 16:41.053
That's what people think?

16:41.100 --> 16:42.419
I did not say "people."

16:42.460 --> 16:44.098
I said "conspiracy theorists."

16:44.130 --> 16:45.722
Proud members
of the tinfoil hat brigade.

16:45.770 --> 16:49.160
Now, this was the shooter;
his name is Ronald Jones.

16:49.200 --> 16:52.067
His victims had just taken
the oath of citizenship.

16:52.110 --> 16:53.270
They were Chris Corwin,

16:53.310 --> 16:57.098
Nick Welden, Pete Goswin
and Leo Stavo.

16:57.150 --> 16:59.539
But some people believe
that these were aliases

16:59.580 --> 17:01.571
given to them
by the American government

17:01.620 --> 17:04.282
before a rogue agent
wiped them out.

17:04.320 --> 17:05.810
You don't really
believe that, right?

17:05.850 --> 17:08.182
No. But it doesn't matter
what I believe.

17:08.220 --> 17:10.654
The question is:
did Fred Kirby believe it?

17:10.690 --> 17:12.555
History is full
of imbeciles

17:12.590 --> 17:14.455
whose outlandish theories
have got them killed,

17:14.500 --> 17:17.128
so perhaps he shared his with
one of the victims' loved ones,

17:17.170 --> 17:18.319
and they took it poorly.

17:18.370 --> 17:19.723
Well, talking
to loved ones

17:19.770 --> 17:21.237
is one thing.

17:21.270 --> 17:22.794
Fred Kirby was trying
to get his hands

17:22.840 --> 17:24.831
on the victims'
personal effects.

17:24.870 --> 17:26.406
He stole mini-Constitutions
with their blood on it.

17:26.440 --> 17:28.374
Why?

17:28.410 --> 17:31.174
If these men really were
nuclear saboteurs,

17:31.210 --> 17:33.371
then their DNA
would've been damaged.

17:33.420 --> 17:35.513
Traces of caesium-137

17:35.550 --> 17:38.280
would mark their remains
for hundreds of years.

17:38.320 --> 17:40.754
The question of where
a low-rent private eye would go

17:40.790 --> 17:44.248
to test for such a thing
is another matter entirely.

17:44.290 --> 17:46.281
No, it isn't.

17:46.330 --> 17:49.299
I think I might know
where he would go.

17:51.230 --> 17:54.097
Yeah, I knew Fred. He's in my
bowling league. We're friends.

17:55.140 --> 17:57.165
He's dead, huh?

17:57.210 --> 17:58.768
Fred specialized
in cheating spouses,

17:58.810 --> 18:00.835
the kind who leave stains
in cheap motel rooms.

18:00.880 --> 18:02.233
I imagine, occasionally,

18:02.280 --> 18:04.748
he needed you to run
a DNA sample for him.

18:04.780 --> 18:07.146
WATSON: When I went through
Fred's financials yesterday,

18:07.180 --> 18:09.319
I noticed he wrote quite a few
checks to you over the years.

18:09.350 --> 18:10.612
Just you.

18:10.650 --> 18:12.584
Never to East Rutherford
Laboratories.

18:12.620 --> 18:14.178
You were giving him a discount

18:14.220 --> 18:15.414
and pocketing
the payments yourself.

18:15.460 --> 18:17.325
No, that's not true.

18:17.360 --> 18:19.453
We also went through Fred's
phone records yesterday.

18:19.490 --> 18:21.526
He talked to you
six times last week.

18:21.560 --> 18:24.120
Can we assume it was
about the blood samples

18:29.800 --> 18:32.530
(opening drawers)

18:32.570 --> 18:34.800
Hey, what are you doing?

18:34.840 --> 18:37.172
Mr. Drexel, we didn't
bring the police with us

18:37.210 --> 18:38.802
because we don't care about

18:38.850 --> 18:40.511
your minor league embezzlement.
We don't.

18:40.550 --> 18:43.189
It was a courtesy to you,
but it also works in our favor,

18:43.220 --> 18:45.211
'cause it means we can conduct
an illegal search

18:45.250 --> 18:47.354
for the materials
that Fred gave you.

18:47.390 --> 18:48.550
Yeah, I'll start
over here.

18:48.590 --> 18:50.251
No,dont.

18:50.290 --> 18:52.429
I'll give you
everything I've got, okay?

18:55.300 --> 18:56.528
The samples,

18:56.560 --> 18:58.562
the results, all of it.

19:02.270 --> 19:04.261
He wasn't checking
for radioactivity,

19:04.310 --> 19:06.301
he was running
paternity tests.

19:06.340 --> 19:08.808
Radioactivity? Why the hell
would I be looking for that?

19:08.840 --> 19:10.740
Fred didn't think that the men
who bled on these documents

19:10.780 --> 19:11.747
were at Chernobyl?

19:11.780 --> 19:13.577
No. God, no.

19:13.620 --> 19:15.349
He gave me that blood sample
and the four Constitutions.

19:15.380 --> 19:17.348
He asked me to
look for a match.

19:17.390 --> 19:18.880
Who's C. Gibson?

19:18.920 --> 19:19.944
I don't have any idea.

19:19.990 --> 19:21.582
I just know the guy
was looking for his father.

19:21.620 --> 19:23.429
But the blood on those
things wasn't viable.

19:23.460 --> 19:25.428
All the_ results came back
inconclu5ive.

19:25.460 --> 19:28.293
If you want to harass someone,
you should go find him.

19:28.330 --> 19:29.649
Why's that?

19:29.700 --> 19:31.793
Fred was nervous about
breaking the news to him.

19:31.830 --> 19:33.434
Said the guy had a real temper.

19:33.470 --> 19:35.290
I don't know.

19:35.340 --> 19:37.365
Maybe he's the one
who killed Fred.

19:40.710 --> 19:43.577
WATSON: This would be a lot
easier if Fred's Kirby's system

19:43.610 --> 19:46.249
wasn't put stuff in files
ordonT.

19:46.280 --> 19:48.612
Well, credit the man
for consistency.

19:48.650 --> 19:51.539
He was lazy and inept
in all facets of his business.

19:51.590 --> 19:52.841
Still, C. Gibson's
full name's got to be

19:52.890 --> 19:53.857
in here somewhere here, right?

19:53.890 --> 19:55.517
Yes, finally.

19:55.560 --> 19:56.788
You found it?

19:56.820 --> 19:59.527
Better. I found years
of annual reports

19:59.560 --> 20:02.449
of Fred Kirby's time
on the board of NYOOPI.

20:02.500 --> 20:03.990
Why would you want that?

20:04.030 --> 20:05.998
Because I hope to find evidence
of embezzlement or fraud.

20:06.030 --> 20:08.294
Let's see how many people
pay for that preposterous

20:08.340 --> 20:11.662
silver star when it becomes
a mark of corruption.

20:11.710 --> 20:13.234
NYOOPI helps people
find detectives.

20:13.280 --> 20:15.373
Why do you have
a problem with that?

20:15.410 --> 20:17.344
Because I want people
to be able to find detectives

20:17.380 --> 20:19.348
who've earned the right
to be called detectives.

20:19.380 --> 20:20.449
Well, if it were up to you,
there'd only be

20:20.480 --> 20:21.879
four or five people like that
in the whole world.

20:21.920 --> 20:23.444
Your point?

20:23.490 --> 20:26.709
If NYOOPI offends you so much,
why don't you just quit?

20:26.750 --> 20:28.957
Because then I won't be able
to pull it apart,

20:28.990 --> 20:30.651
piece by piece, from the inside.

20:30.690 --> 20:32.521
Has it ever occurred to you

20:32.560 --> 20:34.528
that all this righteous
indignation has less to do

20:34.560 --> 20:36.528
with a bunch of private eyes
supporting each other,

20:36.560 --> 20:38.369
and more to do with Shinwell?

20:38.400 --> 20:40.368
What happened
upset you.

20:40.400 --> 20:41.992
And despite a string of
meaningless sexual conquests,

20:42.040 --> 20:44.406
you're still upset,
so now you're gonna take it out

20:44.440 --> 20:46.658
on a bunch of
less talented detectives.

20:46.710 --> 20:48.371
My motives are irrelevant.

20:48.410 --> 20:51.049
NYOOPI is the lowest form
of fake credentialism

20:51.080 --> 20:52.638
and it ought not to exist.

20:52.680 --> 20:54.341
And by the time I'm finished,
it won't.

20:54.380 --> 20:55.847
Where are you going?

20:55.880 --> 20:58.440
The "C" in C. Gibson
stood for Carter.

20:58.490 --> 21:00.355
I found his name and address
ten minutes ago.

21:00.390 --> 21:02.017
I just lingered
to look for these.

21:05.460 --> 21:07.496
BELL:
Here's your tea.

21:07.530 --> 21:10.499
Two lumps. Now you got
to tell me what's up.

21:10.530 --> 21:14.534
Thanks. So, our victims, Fred
Kirby and the missing driver,

21:14.570 --> 21:16.629
were working for a man
named Carter Gibson.

21:16.670 --> 21:19.332
Now, I could not find
a link between that name

21:19.370 --> 21:20.974
and the Bennet_t Courthouse
shoobng,

