25:43.840 --> 25:45.660
Recipients of

25:45.710 --> 25:47.837
the Connecting
My Talents Award receive

25:47.880 --> 25:49.836
a commemorative marble orb.

25:49.880 --> 25:52.041
What's a tooth coalition?

25:52.080 --> 25:55.049
Tooth is a surname,
as are Charcot and Marie.

25:55.080 --> 25:56.638
They're the doctors
who first described

25:56.680 --> 25:58.045
the neurological disorder

25:58.090 --> 26:00.911
which is now
more commonly known as CMT.

26:00.960 --> 26:04.179
CMT attacks
the peripheral nervous system,

26:04.230 --> 26:05.959
arms, legs, hands and feet.

26:05.990 --> 26:08.720
It's degenerative and the
symptoms get worse over time.

26:08.760 --> 26:11.593
Now, if Carter Gibson had it,
it would explain

26:11.630 --> 26:12.961
the orthopedic braces

26:13.000 --> 26:15.230
and probably the medications
he was taking.

26:15.270 --> 26:18.137
So, Carter raised money
and awareness for his disease

26:18.170 --> 26:20.809
and the coalition
gave him one of those.

26:20.840 --> 26:21.829
They gave him two.

26:21.880 --> 26:23.131
These photographs tell us

26:23.180 --> 26:27.105
that he received the award
in 2013 and 2015.

26:27.150 --> 26:30.119
The older one is missing.

26:30.150 --> 26:32.084
And you think it's because
the killer took it with him

26:32.120 --> 26:34.111
after he used it to
bash two skulls in?

26:34.160 --> 26:37.084
He grabbed it there
and started swinging?

26:37.120 --> 26:39.384
The blood evidence
would indicate that.

26:39.430 --> 26:42.729
An arcing motion
like this...

26:43.830 --> 26:44.797
(exhales sharply)

26:44.830 --> 26:47.731
...would result in
blood splatter like that.

26:47.770 --> 26:51.228
So, now we know how the mess
was made, but who made it?

26:53.070 --> 26:55.174
GREGSON:
How's it going?

26:55.210 --> 26:58.099
Slowly, but we think
we figured out the real reason

26:58.150 --> 27:00.812
that Carter Gibson was looking
for his biological father.

27:00.850 --> 27:03.683
I just got off the phone
with Leonard Jones,

27:03.720 --> 27:05.142
Ronald Jones's father.

27:05.190 --> 27:06.009
I was calling
to notify him

27:06.050 --> 27:07.415
that we think his
grandson, Carter,

27:07.450 --> 27:08.849
was the victim
of a homicide.

27:08.890 --> 27:10.721
He didn't take
it too hard.

27:10.760 --> 27:12.887
Apparently, they'd been
estranged most of Carter's life.

27:12.930 --> 27:14.898
WATSON: That changed
earlier this year.

27:14.930 --> 27:16.352
Carter's CMT was getting worse.

27:16.400 --> 27:19.369
The disease is inherited
and the symptoms tend to follow

27:19.400 --> 27:20.958
a similar course
Within families.

27:21.000 --> 27:23.059
Now, no one on
his mother's side had it,

27:23.100 --> 27:24.806
so Carter reached out
to his paternal grandfather

27:24.840 --> 27:26.808
to find out
what he could expect.

27:26.840 --> 27:30.003
Thing is, there was no CMT on
that side of the family, either.

27:30.040 --> 27:32.349
How is that possible?
BELL:
30 years ago,

27:32.380 --> 27:34.940
no one really knew why Ronald
Jones shot up the courthouse

27:34.980 --> 27:36.242
where his wife worked,

27:36.280 --> 27:38.714
but Grandpa Leonard
always had a sneaking suspicion.

27:38.750 --> 27:42.049
Ronald had figured out
he wasn't Carter's real dad.

27:42.090 --> 27:44.081
That would explain some things,
like why the four people

27:44.130 --> 27:46.155
he killed and the six
he wounded were all men.

27:46.190 --> 27:48.249
He thought one of them
was sleeping with his wife.

27:48.300 --> 27:49.949
BELL:
It's an old secret,

27:50.000 --> 27:52.719
but maybe someone figured
it was still worth killing over.

27:52.770 --> 27:54.328
WATSON: We were just
about to call the relatives

27:54.370 --> 27:55.735
of the people who filed
restraining orders

27:55.770 --> 27:57.067
against Fred Kirby,

27:57.100 --> 27:58.806
see if any of them
had CMT.

27:58.840 --> 28:00.262
Just tread lightly.

28:00.310 --> 28:03.006
If one of them did this,
we don't want to tip them.

28:03.040 --> 28:05.008
(knocking on door)

28:06.050 --> 28:07.472
Mr. Garmendia.

28:07.510 --> 28:09.444
Sorry to stop by
unannounced like this,

28:09.480 --> 28:11.345
but your address
is in our files.

28:11.390 --> 28:13.187
If you're looking for an update
on the investigation

28:13.220 --> 28:15.188
of Fred Kirby's murder,
I'm afraid I can't help you.

28:15.220 --> 28:16.380
There have been
some developments,

28:16.420 --> 28:18.081
but they need
to remain confidential.

28:18.130 --> 28:19.381
I don't want an update.

28:19.430 --> 28:23.127
I'm here to talk to you,
detective to detective.

28:27.430 --> 28:32.003
I know you broke into
NYOOPI's computer today.

28:32.040 --> 28:34.372
Someone used
Fred Kirby's old log-in

28:34.410 --> 28:37.470
from an LP. address
inside the NYPD,

28:37.510 --> 28:38.875
and then they downloaded

28:38.910 --> 28:42.277
a bunch of our
tax records.

28:42.320 --> 28:45.209
I could tell you didn't
like us when we met.

28:45.250 --> 28:47.957
Got the feeling
we embarrass you.

28:47.990 --> 28:50.515
You want to tell me
what you're up to?

28:50.560 --> 28:52.255
It's quite simple, really.

28:52.290 --> 28:54.190
I'm going to dismantle
your organization.

28:54.230 --> 28:56.357
NYOOPI is a blight

28:56.400 --> 28:57.799
on the profession which I love.

28:57.830 --> 28:59.195
It enables con men and imbeciles

28:59.230 --> 29:01.130
to pass themselves off
as detectives.

29:01.170 --> 29:02.762
Your group deserves
to be exposed

29:02.800 --> 29:04.529
as the rubber stamp that it is.

29:04.570 --> 29:07.835
Would it surprise you to know

29:07.880 --> 29:10.132
that I agree with you
about NYOOPI?

29:10.180 --> 29:12.148
Hmm?

29:12.180 --> 29:16.344
I was an investigator
for the ATF for over 15 years

29:16.380 --> 29:17.938
before I went private.

29:17.990 --> 29:19.412
I get steamed when I see

29:19.450 --> 29:21.509
the kind of folks
that are advertising

29:21.560 --> 29:24.188
with our silver star.

29:24.230 --> 29:27.381
That's why I got involved,
only I don't want to destroy it.

29:27.430 --> 29:29.227
I want to turn it around.

29:29.260 --> 29:31.399
We're offering
training seminars now.

29:31.430 --> 29:33.796
We just launched a message board

29:33.840 --> 29:36.138
where people can
crowdsource their cases.

29:37.870 --> 29:39.337
I want NYOOPI
to help its members

29:39.370 --> 29:41.406
be better at what they do.

29:41.440 --> 29:43.169
Your members want to be better?

29:43.210 --> 29:44.507
A lot of them mean well.

29:44.550 --> 29:45.903
That's not what I asked.

29:45.950 --> 29:47.247
How many of them
are attending your classes?

29:47.280 --> 29:48.542
How many are on
the message board?

29:48.580 --> 29:50.980
All I'm asking for
is a little more time.

29:51.020 --> 29:52.339
NYOOPI's had decades.

29:52.390 --> 29:53.982
Not with me they haven't.

29:54.020 --> 29:57.387
Look, Mr. Holmes,
this-this thing we do,

29:57.420 --> 29:59.251
this job, it's important.

29:59.290 --> 30:02.191
Now, you say you don't like
a lot of our membership.

30:02.230 --> 30:05.199
I get that, but at least
they're in one place now.

30:05.230 --> 30:07.369
NYOOPI goes away, and
they scatter in the wind.

30:07.400 --> 30:09.459
And I won't know if I
could've made them better.

30:09.500 --> 30:13.869
I won't know if I could've
kept a few from getting killed.

30:13.910 --> 30:16.401
Now, it's too late
for Fred Kirby,

30:16.440 --> 30:19.079
but it's not too late
for the rest.

30:19.110 --> 30:23.342
All I can promise you is that
your organization will be spared

30:23.380 --> 30:27.248
my full energies until I have
solved Fred Kirby's murder.

30:27.290 --> 30:29.110
(sighs) Well, I know
how good you are,

30:29.160 --> 30:32.027
so I guess that doesn't
give me much time.

30:32.060 --> 30:34.893
Thanks for
hearing me out.

30:47.640 --> 30:48.971
(thud in distance)

30:49.010 --> 30:51.399
Sherlock?

30:51.450 --> 30:53.270
HOLMES:
In your bedroom.

30:59.320 --> 31:01.880
Hello.

31:01.920 --> 31:03.888
Okay, whatever this is,

31:03.930 --> 31:05.989
does it really need
to be happening in my bedroom?

31:06.030 --> 31:08.999
This is helping me determine
how much force was used

31:09.030 --> 31:11.590
to beat Carter Gibson
and Fred Kirby to death.

31:11.630 --> 31:13.427
I didn't think you'd mind.

31:13.470 --> 31:15.631
Okay, so, you've already
made one miscalculation.

31:15.670 --> 31:18.036
So, how is the rest
of your math going?

31:18.070 --> 31:20.538
Take this.

31:20.570 --> 31:23.130
Yeah.

31:23.180 --> 31:26.547
That spatter pattern
I've painted in black there,

31:26.580 --> 31:30.414
how far is it from Mr. Coconut?

31:33.490 --> 31:36.914
17 feet, seven inches.

31:36.960 --> 31:40.521
That is precisely the distance
that blood and viscera traveled

31:40.560 --> 31:42.653
from the bookcase
to the far wall

31:42.700 --> 31:45.624
at the murder scene
in Carter Gibson's apartment.

31:45.670 --> 31:48.537
Okay, so why did you think
to check that?

31:48.570 --> 31:50.458
Because it is one of the most
distant blood spatters

31:50.500 --> 31:52.229
I've ever encountered.

31:52.270 --> 31:54.409
So distant, in fact,
that efforts to recreate it

31:54.440 --> 31:57.375
with my own arms
have fallen decidedly short.

31:57.410 --> 31:59.503
Maybe you need a stronger arm.

31:59.550 --> 32:01.609
Between an adolescence
spent at the cricket ground

32:01.650 --> 32:03.515
and two decades training
in the combat arts,

32:03.550 --> 32:05.643
my arm strength
is a little above average.

32:06.720 --> 32:09.518
Now, this tropical drupe
is filled with

32:09.560 --> 32:11.482
a synthetic blood
of my own design.

32:11.530 --> 32:13.998
And I'm gonna murder it...
(clears throat)

32:14.030 --> 32:15.725
with a candlepin bowling ball,

32:15.760 --> 32:17.352
which is almost
identical in Size

32:17.400 --> 32:19.664
and weight to the marble award
that was used.

32:34.480 --> 32:35.674
(grunting)

32:41.160 --> 32:42.513
Not even close.

32:42.560 --> 32:45.586
My best effort,
when my arms were still fresh,

32:45.630 --> 32:49.396
created a blood spatter
which reached 14.3 feet.

32:49.430 --> 32:51.660
Okay, so...

32:51.700 --> 32:55.238
_ our killer is a contestant
in the world's strongest man?

32:55.270 --> 32:56.760
Not quite. (sniffles)

32:56.800 --> 33:00.167
This experiment has shown
that creating that pattern

33:00.210 --> 33:01.529
requires power

33:01.580 --> 33:03.571
and form.

33:03.610 --> 33:05.771
The force and motion required
to create the spatter pattern

33:05.810 --> 33:08.415
at Carter Gibson's apartment
are commensurate with

33:08.450 --> 33:10.611
throwing a 98 mile-an-hour
fastball.

33:10.650 --> 33:13.210
That's major league heat.

33:13.250 --> 33:15.616
Yeah, which is precisely
why our killer

33:15.660 --> 33:18.720
is on the verge of making
major league millions.

33:18.760 --> 33:21.194
You told me about him
the other day.

33:24.170 --> 33:26.195
HOUSTON: You thinkI look
like this Carter guy?

33:26.230 --> 33:28.334
WATSON:
A little.

33:28.370 --> 33:30.531
You both have
your father's ears.

33:30.570 --> 33:33.368
Your dad had an affair
with Rita Dunwitty.

33:33.410 --> 33:34.775
Carter's mom.

33:34.810 --> 33:36.368
He was your
half-brother.

33:36.410 --> 33:38.139
Now, you can deny it
if you want,

33:38.180 --> 33:40.740
but we're gonna order
a DNA test to confirm.

33:43.380 --> 33:45.814
I don't believe anything
you're saying.

33:45.850 --> 33:48.387
But, if it's true, so what?

33:48.420 --> 33:50.251
It's why you
killed him.

33:50.290 --> 33:51.382
Along with the
detective he hired

33:51.430 --> 33:53.125
to find his
real father.

33:53.160 --> 33:54.593
WATSON: Carter grew up
thinking that his father

33:54.630 --> 33:56.518
was a mass shooter.

33:56.560 --> 33:58.699
It followed him around
like a dark cloud.

33:58.730 --> 34:00.459
We think that Fred Kirby
uncovered evidence

34:00.500 --> 34:01.728
of the affair.

34:01.770 --> 34:03.397
Now, if we're right,

34:03.440 --> 34:05.169
and Carter could prove
that his real father

34:05.210 --> 34:07.428
was actually the hero
who stopped the shooting,

34:07.470 --> 34:08.505
he probably couldn't wait
to tell the world.

34:08.540 --> 34:11.145
That was gonna be a real problem
for you, wasn't it?

34:11.180 --> 34:13.842
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

34:13.880 --> 34:15.848
We're talking about CMT.

34:15.880 --> 34:17.313
What?

34:17.350 --> 34:19.215
Charcot_-Marie-Tooth
disease.

34:19.250 --> 34:21.286
It's a genetic
neuromuscular disorder.

34:21.320 --> 34:22.856
Carter had it.

34:22.890 --> 34:24.551
And given that it's
passed down paternally,

34:24.590 --> 34:26.353
we're guessing that you do, too.

34:26.390 --> 34:28.620
You knew that if anyone
discovered you had it,

34:28.660 --> 34:30.855
your plans of making millions
as a major league pitcher

34:30.900 --> 34:32.322
would be wiped out.

34:32.370 --> 34:34.793
WATSON: Uh, we can't
imagine a team offering

34:34.840 --> 34:37.195
a big contract to someone
who could wake up one morning

34:37.240 --> 34:40.232
and suddenly lose all feeling
in his throwing arm.

34:40.270 --> 34:42.807
If a well-known CMT
advocate like Carter

34:42.840 --> 34:44.774
shared the news about
finding his real family,

34:44.810 --> 34:47.745
say if he put it out
on social media,

34:47.780 --> 34:49.816
it would've been a matter
of time before someone

34:49.850 --> 34:50.771
put two and two together.

34:50.820 --> 34:52.811
Now, you needed
the whole thing to go away

34:52.850 --> 34:54.715
so you could still cash in.

34:54.760 --> 34:55.818
You guys are crazy.

34:55.860 --> 34:57.816
Forget CMT, look at my ERA.

34:57.860 --> 35:00.249
I'm pitching great; I-I don't
have a muscle disorder.

35:00.290 --> 35:01.757
All right, then,
let's talk about something

35:01.800 --> 35:03.358
you definitely don't have:

35:03.400 --> 35:05.391
an alibi for the night
of the murders.

35:05.430 --> 35:07.660
That's because you were
at Carter's apartment.

35:07.700 --> 35:10.464
He and Fred were telling you
things you didn't want to hear,

35:10.500 --> 35:13.139
so you took Carter's award
down from the shelf,

35:13.170 --> 35:14.899
and you killed them with it.

35:14.940 --> 35:17.272
Only a matter of time
until we find it.

35:17.310 --> 35:20.802
Got to think it'll have your
fingerprints on it when we do.

35:23.820 --> 35:24.809
I need you two.

35:24.850 --> 35:26.545
Now.

35:34.530 --> 35:35.758
What's going on?

35:35.800 --> 35:37.495
He was about to
give it up.

35:37.530 --> 35:39.919
Well, that would've been
a real problem for the DA.

35:39.970 --> 35:41.437
How so?

35:41.470 --> 35:43.461
That's Paul Fontino.

35:43.500 --> 35:45.707
He's Houston's pitching coach.

35:45.740 --> 35:47.731
He just confessed
to both murders.

36:00.290 --> 36:02.451
Sorry about the wait,
Mr. Fontino.

36:02.490 --> 36:04.788
We just had to confirm
there really were bloodstains

36:04.830 --> 36:06.479
in the trunk of your car.

36:06.530 --> 36:09.727
Don't know why you'd think
I'd lie about such a thing.

36:09.760 --> 36:12.263
Maybe because
we can't quite figure out

36:12.300 --> 36:14.234
why you would do such a thing.

36:14.270 --> 36:16.898
You've had two parking
tickets in the last 20 years.

36:16.940 --> 36:18.339
But this past weekend,

36:18.370 --> 36:19.632
you just snap?
(snaps fingers)

36:19.670 --> 36:21.479
Murder two people?

36:21.510 --> 36:25.742
I've been working with
Houston Spivey for six years.

36:25.780 --> 36:29.773
Found him when he was a skinny
little high school sophomore.

36:29.820 --> 36:31.811
He's a good kid.

36:31.850 --> 36:33.647
He's got a hell
of a future.

36:33.690 --> 36:35.749
I didn't want to see it wasted.

36:35.790 --> 36:37.712
What does that mean?
Last week,

36:37.760 --> 36:41.389
he tells me this Carter guy
and his crazy P.I.,

36:41.430 --> 36:43.250
they're after him
for a blood test.

36:43.300 --> 36:45.598
Well, he told us he'd
never seen Carter Gibson

36:45.630 --> 36:46.995
before in his life.

36:47.030 --> 36:49.396
You ever been
21 years old before?

36:49.440 --> 36:50.668
Kid's scared.

36:51.870 --> 36:53.804
I mean, if you think
Houston asked me to do this,

36:53.840 --> 36:55.239
you got the wrong idea.

36:55.280 --> 36:56.929
He wanted to pay them.

36:56.980 --> 36:59.608
He asked me for the money.
What money?

36:59.650 --> 37:02.619
They were extorting him; they
wanted $50,000 to keep quiet.

37:02.650 --> 37:04.686
And they thought Houston,
a college student,

37:04.720 --> 37:06.608
would have 50 grand
lying around?

37:06.650 --> 37:08.686
I'm sure they figured that
a future first rounder

37:08.720 --> 37:10.915
would be able to
get his hands on some money

37:10.960 --> 37:12.382
if he really wanted it.

37:12.430 --> 37:13.954
He probably could've.

37:13.990 --> 37:15.890
But I didn't think
it was right.

37:15.930 --> 37:17.898
I told Houston I'd handle it.

37:17.930 --> 37:20.319
So you set up a meeting?

37:20.370 --> 37:21.769
At Carter's apartment.

37:21.800 --> 37:24.268
I thought I'd rant
and rave a little

37:24.310 --> 37:26.835
and get them to back off.

37:26.870 --> 37:28.406
But they weren't budging.

37:28.440 --> 37:29.600
I saw red,

37:29.640 --> 37:31.540
grabbed this...

37:31.580 --> 37:36.517
marble statue thing
off from the shelf...

37:36.550 --> 37:38.313
that was that.

37:40.090 --> 37:41.557
HOLMES:
Well, he's lying obviously.

37:41.590 --> 37:43.387
I mean, it's a tale
as old as time.

37:43.420 --> 37:45.456
Or at least as old
as profe55ional sports.

37:45.490 --> 37:47.287
The sins of the entitled athlete

37:47.330 --> 37:49.548
being swept under the rug
by his enablers.

37:49.600 --> 37:51.420
I'm sure
Mr. Fontino's family

37:51.470 --> 37:54.394
will be enjoying
the blood money he's earning

37:54.440 --> 37:57.398
as soon as Houston Spivey's name
is called in the draft.

37:57.440 --> 37:59.465
Well, the lab says the blood
in Fontino's trunk

37:59.510 --> 38:00.704
was a match for the victims.

38:00.740 --> 38:02.537
And he knew about
the murder weapon.

38:02.580 --> 38:05.344
He knew about it, couldn't
produce it though, could he?

38:05.380 --> 38:07.575
He said he threw it off
the Staten Island Ferry.

38:07.610 --> 38:09.544
Yeah, another lie, no doubt.

38:09.580 --> 38:12.515
Look, I'll concede that he was
an accessory after the fact.

38:12.550 --> 38:13.710
I don't think
there's any coincidence

38:13.750 --> 38:14.956
that the bodies
were disposed of

38:14.990 --> 38:16.685
at his cousin's crematorium,

38:16.720 --> 38:19.723
but I refuse to believe
he's our killer.

38:19.760 --> 38:21.318
Then should've come
with me to the precinct

38:21.360 --> 38:23.328
instead of trying to dig up
more dirt on NYOOPI.

38:23.360 --> 38:25.396
Yes, I should have.

38:25.430 --> 38:26.795
Found what I need, though.

38:26.830 --> 38:28.866
What do you mean?
I mean,

38:28.900 --> 38:32.836
this time tomorrow,
NYOOPI will be no more.

38:32.870 --> 38:36.601
For what it's worth,
Fontino was a college pitcher.

38:36.640 --> 38:38.744
Yes, he was.
That was 45 years ago.

38:38.780 --> 38:40.805
Now he's a retiree
with a herniated disc

38:40.850 --> 38:42.545
and arthritis in both hands.

38:42.580 --> 38:44.582
I mean, he'd have trouble
lifting the murder weapon

38:44.620 --> 38:46.588
above his head, let alone
swinging it hard enough

38:46.620 --> 38:47.848
to send blood flying

38:47.890 --> 38:49.448
across the room.
(loud bang)

38:52.730 --> 38:54.357
That was the sound.

38:54.400 --> 38:55.822
What?

38:55.860 --> 38:57.418
A bang.

38:57.460 --> 38:58.996
Carter's neighbors said
they heard a noise that night,

38:59.030 --> 39:01.533
a bang.

39:04.440 --> 39:06.362
Thanks for coming
in, Mr. Spivey.

39:06.410 --> 39:08.401
I don't understand
why I'm here again.

39:08.440 --> 39:09.634
When I gave my statement
about Coach Fontino,

39:09.680 --> 39:11.545
my lavwer said that would be it.

39:11.580 --> 39:12.945
WATSON: He's right,
you don't have to say

39:12.980 --> 39:14.470
anything today.

39:14.520 --> 39:15.839
I'm just curious,
um, do you know

39:15.880 --> 39:17.973
what the worst pitch
you ever threw was?

39:18.020 --> 39:21.683
Uh, gave up a two-run double
in the playoffs last year.

39:21.720 --> 39:23.153
Hung a curve.

39:23.190 --> 39:24.452
Actually,

39:24.490 --> 39:26.526
it was when you
flung the murder weapon

39:26.560 --> 39:29.449
from the scene of the
double homicide you committed.

39:32.430 --> 39:34.398
(bang)
BELL: Two of
Carter Gibson's neighbors

39:34.440 --> 39:37.694
heard a bang like that the night
he and Fred Kirby were killed.

39:37.740 --> 39:39.537
They thought it was
a car backfiring.

39:39.570 --> 39:40.798
We wondered if maybe

39:40.840 --> 39:42.876
it was a gunshot.

39:42.910 --> 39:45.140
Turns out, it was the sound
of a perfect strike.

39:45.180 --> 39:46.477
GREGSON:
You left tracks

39:46.510 --> 39:48.512
at the scene.

39:48.550 --> 39:50.814
Bloody footprints
from Carter's door

39:50.850 --> 39:52.943
to your coach's car.

39:52.990 --> 39:54.810
Stood to reason
you took the murder weapon

39:54.860 --> 39:57.511
along with the bodies.

39:57.560 --> 39:58.788
Only you didn't.

39:58.830 --> 40:00.855
You threw it 245 feet

40:00.890 --> 40:02.448
into that Dumpster.

40:02.500 --> 40:03.899
WATSON :
It's pretty impressive.

40:03.930 --> 40:06.819
But like I said, it was
the worst pitch of your life.

40:06.870 --> 40:09.589
The blood of both victims
and your fingerprints

40:09.640 --> 40:10.493
are all over it.

40:10.540 --> 40:11.905
What happened?

40:11.940 --> 40:13.669
Did you think
you heard someone coming?

40:13.710 --> 40:16.099
You panicked, threw it
as far as you could?

40:20.650 --> 40:24.017
I'd like my lavwer now, please.

40:27.750 --> 40:29.752
Sherlock?

40:29.790 --> 40:31.018
(groans)

40:31.060 --> 40:32.687
Is that why
you called me down here,

40:32.730 --> 40:36.052
to troll me again for
enrolling us in NYOOPI?

40:36.100 --> 40:38.466
Gonna mark you down a point
for poor observational skills.

40:38.500 --> 40:39.489
Look more closely.

40:41.070 --> 40:43.061
WATSON:
"ESOOPI"?

40:46.140 --> 40:47.607
He has agreed to shutter
the organization,

40:47.640 --> 40:49.631
as I predicted
he would.

40:49.680 --> 40:53.104
But, like a phoenix
rising from the dung heap,

40:53.150 --> 40:56.119
a new trade organization has
been born to take its place:

40:56.150 --> 40:58.072
ESOOPI.

40:58.120 --> 41:00.247
The Empire State Order
of Private Investigators.

41:00.290 --> 41:02.087
All members of
the former NYOOPI

41:02.120 --> 41:03.883
will be allowed
to stay on.

41:03.920 --> 41:05.785
And Mr. Garmendia will be
retaining his position

41:05.830 --> 41:07.058
as president.

41:07.090 --> 41:08.853
Is that what you meant
when you said

41:08.900 --> 41:10.026
NYOOPI would be no more?

41:10.060 --> 41:11.823
So what's the point?

41:11.870 --> 41:13.519
Now there's a group
that's gonna be handing out

41:13.570 --> 41:15.094
gold stars
instead of silver ones?

41:15.140 --> 41:18.132
No. Nothing will be handed out.

41:18.170 --> 41:20.968
Gold stars and a listing on the
group's all-important Web site

41:21.010 --> 41:22.500
will be earned

41:22.540 --> 41:25.270
by members who complete a
course of my own design.

41:25.310 --> 41:28.177
It's compulsory, not optional.

41:28.210 --> 41:30.144
You really think
1,200 dues-paying members

41:30.180 --> 41:32.080
are gonna sit still
for that?

41:32.120 --> 41:34.179
I don't believe they're
gonna have a choice.

41:34.220 --> 41:35.687
I spent all of yesterday

41:35.720 --> 41:37.517
poring over the bylaws
that they agreed to

41:37.560 --> 41:39.926
when they joined;
NYOOPI is more than allowed

41:39.960 --> 41:42.224
to change its name
and its standards.

41:42.260 --> 41:43.898
And any members
that don't appreciate

41:43.930 --> 41:45.568
that kind of attention to detail

41:45.600 --> 41:47.124
will learn to.

41:47.170 --> 41:49.092
Or they'll forfeit
their membership.

41:49.140 --> 41:50.664
Is that...?

41:50.700 --> 41:52.304
The test, yes.

41:52.340 --> 41:55.002
I thought you would be honored
to be the first ESOOPI member

41:55.040 --> 41:56.029
to attempt it.

41:58.610 --> 42:00.999
"List three suitable methods
for determining the age

42:01.050 --> 42:02.574
of a fecal deposit on a..."

42:02.620 --> 42:04.110
This is the first question?

42:04.150 --> 42:06.243
Two hours, Watson.
(knocks on desk)

42:06.290 --> 42:07.746
Make me proud.

42:07.790 --> 42:11.055
*

42:11.090 --> 42:14.799
* Lurch around the room

42:14.830 --> 42:16.991
* You know you got the right.

